<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-17T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2296: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-17T11:00:00+01:00">September 17, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received September 17—7:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>84. Your 62, September 15, 11 a.m. <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> says that he will start this in motion. He
                                adds that it would be very helpful to him and perhaps prevent his
                                making a slip if you could be good enough to give him for his
                                confidential information if advisable, <pb facs="0334" n="230" xml:id="pg_230"/>
                                <list>
                                    <label>1.</label>
                                    <item>Your views on this subject, which party is most
                                        recalcitrant, your general policy, et cetera.</item>
                                    <label>2.</label>
                                    <item>The details of the plan which the Commission of Neutrals
                                        is now endeavoring to make the two parties accept.</item>
                                    <label>3.</label>
                                    <item>Information as to the progress of your negotiations from
                                        time to time as they take place.</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>